            <div class="founder-bio">
              <p>
                Che-Yu is a new media artist who believes algorithmic art is not about making computers draw, 
                but about designing the rules of life. His work explores digital life, the beauty of mathematics, 
                and the possibilities of human-machine symbiosis. He has participated in the Venice Biennale, 
                Art Basel Miami, and Paris 104 residency, with representative works including the Taipei 101 
                solo exhibition "Formula of Everything" and the immersive piano concert "Algorithmic Psalms."
              </p>
            </div>
